		<p>James is currently a Supervisor at The Third Floor, the premiere pevisualization company for the entertainment industry.  James supervised <em>GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY VOL. 2</em> and <em>ANT MAN</em>, for which he received a VES nomination for Virtual Cinematography.  Previously, James supervised previsualisation on <em>GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY</em> and <em>PARADISE LOST</em>. Before that, he was Previs Lead on <em>THOR THE DARK WORLD</em>. In addition, James has also worked on the previs for such films as <em>X MEN: DAYS OF FUTURE PAST</em>, <em>THE AVENGERS</em>, <em>SAN ANDREAS</em>, <em>POLTERGEIST (2015)</em>, <em>JACK THE GIANT SLAYER</em>, <em>47 RONIN</em>, <em>300: RISE OF AN EMPIRE</em> and <em>JOURNEY 2: THE MYSTERIOUS ISLAND</em> as well as supervising 4 video game cinematics. Prior to The Third Floor, James was an animator at Sony on the features <em>OPEN SEASON</em>, <em>BEOWULF</em>, <em>I AM LEGEND</em> and <em>CLOUDY WITH A CHANCE OF MEATBALLS</em>. James began his career at Disney. He enjoyed a nine year run animating on such memorable characters as Hades (James Woods) in <em>HERCULES</em>, Mushu (Eddie Murphy) in <em>MULAN</em>, Kuzco (David Spade) in <em>THE EMPEROR'S NEW GROOVE</em>, as well as having worked on such films as <em>POCAHONTAS</em>, <em>THE HUNCHBACK OF NOTRE DAME</em>, <em>TARZAN</em>, <em>FANTASIA 2000</em>, <em>TREASURE PLANET</em> and <em>BOLT</em>. In addition, he worked on <em>LOONEY TUNES: BACK IN ACTION</em> for Warner Bros., animating three of the world’s most recognizable cartoon characters – Bugs Bunny, Daffy Duck and Marvin the Martian. Being multi-faceted, James had worked on music videos and documentaries as well as having directed several short films, including the multi-awarding winning <em>ANIMATED AMERICAN</em>.</p>

